"present_1mp", "form": "نُضْحِي", "in_corpus": true, "count": 1, "asp": "i", "per": "1", "gen": "m", "num": "p"}, {"role": "past_1mp", "form": "أَضْحَيْنا", "in_corpus": false, "count": null, "asp": "p", "per": "1", "gen": "m", "num": "p"}, {"role": "past_1ms", "form": "أَضْحَيْتُ", "in_corpus": false, "count": null, "asp": "p", "per": "1", "gen": "m", "num": "s"}], "frequency_in_corpus": 62, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 2, "pos_tags": ["noun", "verb"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 4}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n25618", "n25630"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B6%D9%92%D8%AD%D9%8E%D9%89"}}, "translations": {"en": "to become morning", "fa": "صبح شدن", "ur": "صبح ہونا", "tr": "sabah olmak", "id": "menjadi pagi", "bn": "সকাল হওয়া", "es": "hacerse mañana", "fr": "devenir matin", "de": "morgen werden", "ru": "становиться утром", "zh": "成为早晨"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "sacrificial animal, victim", "tags": ["collective"]}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to become", "tags": ["copulative"], "examples": [{"text": "أَضْحَى الطَّالِبُ نَشِيطًا", "english": "The student became hardworking."}]}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to make visible"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to set out (to do something), to commence (doing something)"}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "From ضَحَّى (ḍaḥḥā, “sacrifice, immolate”).\n\nFrom ضَحْوَة (ḍaḥwa, “morning”), from the root ض ح و (ḍ ḥ w). Sense of “become” resembles other verbs of similar meaning derived from different times of day; compare أَصْبَحَ (ʔaṣbaḥa), بَاتَ (bāta), أَمْسَى (ʔamsā), all meaning \"become.\""}, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n25618", "headword_ar": "اضحى", "root": "DHw and DHY", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(a man, TA)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "entered upon the time of morning called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlD~uHaY", "text_ar": "الضُّحَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K, * TA,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the time called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlD~aHowap", "text_ar": "الضَّحْوَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,) [or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the time called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlD~aHaA='", "text_ar": "الضَّحَا=ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", for] you say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aqamotu biAlmakaAni Hat~aY A^aDoHayotu", "text_ar": "اَقَمْتُ بِالمَكَانِ حَتَّى اَضْحَيْتُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlD~aHaA='u", "text_ar": "الضَّحَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[and therefore meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I remained in the place until I entered upon the time called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlD~aHaA='", "text_ar": "الضَّحَا=ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], like as you say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aSobaHotu", "text_ar": "اَصْبَحْتُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlS~abaAHu", "text_ar": "الصَّبَاحُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S, TA.) Hence the saying of 'Omar,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aDoHuwA", "text_ar": "اَضْحُوا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "liSalaApi AlD~uHaY", "text_ar": "لِصَلَاةِ الضُّحَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biSalaApi AlD~uHaY", "text_ar": "بِصَلَاةِ الضُّحَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,) i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Perform ye the prayer of the time called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlDHY", "text_ar": "الضحى"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "at its"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "proper"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "time:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "do not delay it until the time called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlD~aHaA='", "text_ar": "الضَّحَا=ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "has become advanced: (TA:) or do not perform that prayer when the time called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlD~uHaY", "text_ar": "الضُّحَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "has become advanced. (S.) ―         -b2-  And you say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ADHY fulaAnN yafoEalu ka*aA", "text_ar": "اضحى فُلَانٌ يَفْعَلُ كَذَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, M, K,) like as you say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Zal~a yfEl k*A", "text_ar": "ظَلَّ يفعل كذا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S;) meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a one became occupied,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "engaged, in the time called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlD~uHaY", "text_ar": "الضُّحَى"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in doing such a thing:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, K, TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "did such a thing in the first part of the day,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IKtt, TA.) ―         -b3-  [This phrase often means also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a one became occupied,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "engaged, in doing such a thing; betook, set,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "applied, himself to doing such a thing; set about,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "commenced, doing such a thing;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "began to do such a thing;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aSobaHa", "text_ar": "اَصْبَحَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Zal~a", "text_ar": "ظَلَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c. And, like these verbs,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ADHY", "text_ar": "اضحى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "followed by an aor., or by a part. n. in the accus. case, often requires to be rendered simply"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it, became:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "see an ex. in a verse cited voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dafiy^N", "text_ar": "دَفِيٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] ―         -b4-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ADHY", "text_ar": "اضحى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He performed the supererogatory act of prayer"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aln~aAfilap", "text_ar": "النَّافِلَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the time called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlD~uHaY", "text_ar": "الضُّحَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) ―         -b5-  See also 1, last sentence but one. ―         -b6-  One says also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ADHY Eani AlA^amori", "text_ar": "اضحى عَنِ الاَمْرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He withdrew himself far from the affair."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA. [See also another meaning of this phrase in what follows.]) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlqaTA yuDoHiY Eani AlmaA='i", "text_ar": "القَطا يُضْحِى عَنِ المَا=ءِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The birds called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qTA", "text_ar": "قطا"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "go far from water."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.)       -A2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ADHY Al$~aYo'a", "text_ar": "اضحى الشَّىْءَ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He made apparent, showed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "revealed, the thing."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eani AlA^amori", "text_ar": "عَنِ الاَمْرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "DH~Y", "text_ar": "ضحّى", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He made the affair,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "case, apparent,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "manifest:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and [so"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ADHY Eanohu", "text_ar": "اضحى عَنْهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", for] one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aDoHi liY Eano A^amorika", "text_ar": "اَضْحِ لِى عَنْ اَمْرِكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", with fet-h to the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "'", "text_ar": "ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Make manifest to me thy affair,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "case:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so in the M. (TA.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA A^aDoHaY", "text_ar": "لَا اَضْحَى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A@ll~`hu lanaA Zil~aka", "text_ar": "ا@للّٰهُ لَنَا ظِلَّكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a deprecatory phrase [lit."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "May God not cause thy shadow to become sun to us:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "meaning (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "may God not deprive us of thee by death:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "DaHaA Zil~uhu", "text_ar": "ضَحَا ظِلُّهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":) or it may be similar in meaning to the phrase here following]. (TA.)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA tuDoHinaA", "text_ar": "لَا تُضْحِنَا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eano Zil~ika", "text_ar": "عَنْ ظِلِّكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[lit."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Make us not to go forth into the sun from thy shadow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] means (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "withdraw not from us the shadow of thy compassion:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the verb being made trans. by means of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "En", "text_ar": "عن"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "because the phrase implies the meaning of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA tuxorijonaA minohu", "text_ar": "لَا تُخْرِجْنَا مِنْهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Zl~", "text_ar": "ظلّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being here used metaphorically. (Har p. 4.)"}], "source_refs": ["TA", "S", "M", "K"]}, {"entry_id": "n25630", "headword_ar": "اَضْحَى", "root": "DHw and DHY", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", applied to a horse,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^a$ohabu", "text_ar": "اَشْهَبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Of a colour in which whiteness predominates over blackness;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.]: fem."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "DaHoyaA='u", "text_ar": "ضَحْيَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S, K:) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlD~aHoyaA='u", "text_ar": "الضَّحْيَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "was, (K,) or was also, (S, and so afterwards in the K,) the name of a certain mare, belonging to 'Amr Ibn-'Ámir (S, K) Ibn-Rabee'ah. (S.) ―         -b2-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "layolapN DaHoyaA='u", "text_ar": "لَيْلَةٌ ضَحْيَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, K,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "DaHoyaA", "text_ar": "ضَحْيَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "with the short"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A", "text_ar": "ا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", both mentioned by ISd, (TA,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iDoHiyaAnapN", "text_ar": "اـِضْحِيَانَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, K,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iDoHiyapN", "text_ar": "اـِضْحِيَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "accord. to the K, but [SM says] I have not found any mention of this last, [meaning except in the K,] and probably the right word is ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iDHiyaAnN", "text_ar": "اـِضحِيَانٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as in the books of strange words together with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "